Description: Kerberos TGT management system tray icon
 krbtray sits in the system tray and monitors the state of all Kerberos
 Ticket-Granting Tickets (TGTs) in the Heimdal credential cache collection.
 .
 Features include:
  - Tray icon colour-coded by worst ticket state (valid/expiring/expired)
  - Automatic TGT renewal a configurable time before expiry
  - Desktop notification on renewal failure
  - GTK3 dialog for obtaining new tickets (kinit)
  - Optional password storage via the system Secret Service (libsecret)
  - Auto-kinit on login using a stored password
  - Multi-principal support via KCM or DIR credential cache types
  - Preferences dialog and XDG autostart integration
 .
 Designed for use on Linux Mint / Cinnamon and other GTK3 desktop
 environments that support GtkStatusIcon (XFCE, MATE, etc.).
